# Phase 35 · Master Meta Mega Final Release

Repository: `cvsz/zdash`

Goal:
Finalize zDash into a production-grade, safety-first, full-stack release candidate by completing source code polish, feature integration, options, functions, backend logic, frontend UI/UX, dashboards, documentation, validation, and release hardening while preserving all safety policies from Phases 01–34.

Do not rebuild the project from scratch. Inspect the repository first, preserve the current architecture, and apply incremental, tested changes only.

---

## Non-negotiable safety invariants

- Do not enable live trading.
- Do not add real broker order execution.
- Do not bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Do not bypass `TradingService`, `ExecutionEngine`, `SignalValidationService`, RBAC, audit/event logging, dry-run mode, or existing zDash safety policy.
- AI Trader remains simulation-only / paper-trading only.
- Content publishing remains approval-gated and dry-run by default.
- Billing provider remains mock by default.
- Stripe remains disabled by default unless explicitly configured outside this phase.
- Marketplace plugin runtime remains sandboxed by default.
- Marketplace review is required by default.
- Enterprise license must never disable `PRODUCTION_SAFETY_LOCK`.
- No raw secrets, `.env`, GPG passphrases, token dumps, private keys, payment secrets, API keys, or Cloudflare tokens may be committed.
- `docs/prompt/codex-runs/` must remain local-only and untracked.
- Backend port is `8005`; do not introduce `localhost:8000` or `BACKEND_PORT=8000` outside archived/local-only prompt artifacts.
- All risky flows must show visible safety copy in UI.
- All financial/trading UI must include simulation-only / not financial advice language.

---

