## Commit

Use one final commit if changes are small and cohesive:

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "phase35: finalize zdash release candidate"
```

If many unrelated fixes are required, split commits by area:

```bash
git commit -m "phase35: harden backend release checks"
git commit -m "phase35: polish frontend release dashboard"
git commit -m "phase35: update final release documentation"
```
